<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Defense Against Allies<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.60)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=8212'>Dan "Gil-galad" H</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=8212&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> January 21, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> These are SHORT articles that help people who need to defend against a certain card or card type that their friend/ playing group is over-using. Please rate understanding that these are not meant to be long. <br>
<br>
Getting sick of PATHS being played twice EVERY turn due to Frodo? Hating how Ru&#39;mil/ Celeborn/ Galadriel is just killing those little Orcs? Here is all of the counters to allies:<br>
<br>
NOTE: many of these cards say &#39;discard an ally&#39; not kill, which means they can be re-played.<br>
<br>
The most obvious ally counter is: <br>
Anduin Confluence Site 7 Cost 6   U 353<br>
Makes all allies be discarded. This is for both players, which may be impracticable if you like your allies.<br>
<br>
Now for a culture by culture break down.<br>
<br>
Isengard:<br>
<br>
1) No Ordinary Storm Cost 1   U 130<br>
Exhausts all Gandalf signet allies to prevent their special abilities.<br>
2) Their Arrows Enrage Cost 1   C 141<br>
All of the archer allies will have much less power, thus being easier to kill when at their home site.<br>
<br>
Moria:<br>
<br>
1) Bitter Hatred Cost 1   U 164<br>
Spot a Marksman or Archer to wound (could kill) an elf (companion or ally)<br>
2) Goblin Warrior Cost 2   C 185<br>
Discard Grimir or Thrarin when played.<br>
<br>
Nazgul:<br>
<br>
1) Beauty Is Fading Cost 5   R 205<br>
If your opponent has no conditions or possessions (early game maybe) then discard an ally or companion.<br>
2) Blade Tip Cost 0   U 209<br>
If at an ally&#39;s home site and you win the skirmish, then drop it on them to cause some damage until death.<br>
3) Fear Cost 1   R 212<br>
Straight up discard an ally.<br>
4) The Nine Servants Of Sauron Cost 1   U 219<br>
When playing a Nazgul, you can exert Bilbo or the Gaffer or whoever to minimize on their play.<br>
5) Their Power Is In Terror Cost 0   U 226<br>
Wounds every one of their allies. Not bad.<br>
<br>
Sauron:<br>
<br>
1) Mordor&#39;s Strength Cost 1   C 255<br>
Wound an ally that a Sauron Orc is skirmishing.<br>
2) Morgul Skirisher Cost3   U 257<br>
Remove 3 twilight to exert a hobbit ally (Bilbo, Gaffer, Bounder, etc.)<br>
3) Any minion that exerts to wound and then wins the skirmish causes 2 wounds.<br>
<br>
Over all, if there is an opportunity to overwhelm that hated Ru&#39;mil at site 6, then it would be wiser to do that instead of MAYBE (PATHS, Intuition, Bounder, etc.) trying to overwhelm Frodo. Any damage adders (like with Sauron) always slow down allies. And when the main ones for each sanctuary (Elrond for 3, Galadriel for 6) are killed, the whole ally strategy takes a down turn. <br>
<br>
Now go ignore Orophin and cause your opponent a lot of Worrying!<br>
<br>
If you want a card to be posted, please d-mail me. <br>
<br>
Dan Hummel <br>
Gil-galad <br>
